1. Admin Dashboard (Landing Page)

Purpose: High-level visibility & quick control

Top Metrics (Real-time cards):

Total Active Users (Students / Tutors / Counselors)

Pending Approvals (Tutors & Counselors)

Upcoming Sessions (Today / This Week)

Pending Booking Requests

Reported Issues (Urgent / Normal)

Average Platform Rating

Sessions Completed (This Month)

Visuals:

Calendar view (all approved sessions)

Alerts panel (urgent issues, no-show spikes, system warnings)

Activity feed (recent approvals, cancellations, reports)

Quick Actions:

Approve Users

Resolve Issues

Broadcast Notification

Suspend Account

2. User Management

Full control over all users

View Users

Filter by:

Role (Student / Tutor / Counselor)

Department

Status (Active / Pending / Suspended)

Rating (Tutors/Counselors)

Each user card shows:

Name + profile picture

School email

Role

Account status

Last login

Number of sessions

Actions:

Approve / Reject tutor or counselor accounts

Suspend / Reactivate users

Reset user password (force reset)

Edit limited profile fields (admin override)

View full activity history

3. Session Management (Global Control)

Admin sees ALL sessions

Displays:

Student name

Tutor/Counselor name

Date & time

Mode (online / in-person)

Status (Upcoming / Completed / Cancelled / No-show)

Reason/request message

Actions:

Cancel session (with reason)

Force reschedule

Mark as completed (admin override)

Flag suspicious activity

View session history per user

Smart Flags:

Repeated cancellations

Frequent no-shows

Overbooking attempts

4. Booking Requests Oversight

Admin visibility into all pending & approved requests

Shows:

Request status

Who approved/rejected

Suggested reschedules

Conflicts (double booking, availability mismatch)

Actions:

Override tutor decisions

Resolve disputes

Approve on behalf of tutor (optional university policy)

5. Ratings & Feedback Management (Quality Assurance)

Critical for universities

View:

All ratings & comments

Average rating per tutor/counselor

Trends (weekly/monthly)

Low-rating alerts (e.g. <3 stars)

Actions:

Flag inappropriate reviews

Remove abusive feedback

Contact tutor/counselor

Request follow-up from student

Generate quality reports for departments

6. Reports & Issue Resolution Center

Centralized issue inbox from students and tutors

Each report shows:

Reporter (student/tutor)

Issue title & description

Priority (Urgent / Normal)

Category (Technical, Behavior, Scheduling)

Related session (if any)

Actions:

Assign issue to admin/support staff

Update status (Open / In Progress / Resolved)

Communicate with reporter

Escalate serious misconduct

Maintain resolution history (audit trail)

7. Notifications & Announcements

Admin-controlled communication

Broadcast Notifications:

To all users

By role (Students only, Tutors only)

By department

Channels:

In-app

Email

SMS (if enabled)

Examples:

Maintenance notices

Policy updates

Exam-period tutoring reminders

8. Approval & Compliance Management

University trust layer

Approve tutors/counselors only after verification

View uploaded qualifications (if required)

Enforce university rules:

Max sessions per week

Allowed locations

Online vs in-person policies

9. Analytics & Reports

Exportable for university leadership

Reports:

Session usage by department

Peak booking times

Tutor performance reports

Student engagement levels

Issue resolution times

Formats:

CSV / PDF

Monthly & semester reports

10. System Settings & Security

Admin-only configuration

Settings:

Allowed university email domains

OTP expiry time

Rate limits (OTP, login attempts)

Enable/disable features (chat, ratings, SMS)

Session duration rules

Security:

Audit logs (logins, changes, approvals)

